<font color="#FF0000">WHISPERING DEATH</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug 29 23:13:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Death,<br><br>
I know you well.  I have teased you all my life.  I have caressed your darkness.  I long for your solitude.  Why have you forsaken me in my times of need.  Why have we not been kinsmen.  I call your name in the night.  I wail at the moon in the dark of the night.<br><br>
I feel the darkness of my soul searching for your touch.  You fear me.  You know what I am and shun me.  You will not allow me to reside in your world.  I am what you are not.  I know no fear.  I feel no remorse.  I have no weakness that you may exploit.<br><br>
I have heard the whispering death.  I know your song.  I reach and you withdraw.  I call you now and there is silence.<br><br>
If you can not meet me in the field of battle then cease your useless words.  I am not the victim you seek.  We will fight our struggle one day and our deaths will be glorious.<br><br>
I am a Silent Warrior
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


